
LSB stands for *Linux Standard Base*.

The goal of the LSB is to make it easy to create binary packages that will run on any → Linux → Linux/distributions[distribution].

The LSB has five separate standards: Common, Core, Desktop, Runtime Languages and Imaging.

→ https://lists.linuxfoundation.org/pipermail/lsb-discuss/2023-February/008278.html[Apparently], LSB is «essentially dead».

{ Core #core

  Bash, Bc, Binutils, Coreutils, Diffutils, File, Findutils, Gawk,
  Grep, GTK+2, Gzip, M4, Man-DB, Ncurses, Procps, Psmisc,
  Sed, Shadow, Tar, Util-linux, → development/compression/zlib.

}

{ Misc

  Version 5.0 has been submitted as ISO/IEC 23360:2021

}

